###

### LogsService API Tests

### 1. Get all logs (Admin only - requires admin authentication)
GET https://localhost:7004/logs
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: application/json

### 2. Get logs by service (Admin only)
GET https://localhost:7004/logs/service/UsersService
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: application/json

### 3. Get logs by service - ProductsService
GET https://localhost:7004/logs/service/ProductsService
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: application/json

### 4. Get logs by level - ERROR
GET https://localhost:7004/logs/level/ERROR
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: application/json

### 5. Get logs by level - INFO
GET https://localhost:7004/logs/level/INFO
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: application/json

### 6. Create new log entry (requires authentication)
POST https://localhost:7004/logs
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "service": "TestService",
    "level": "INFO",
    "message": "Test log message created via API"
}

### 7. Get logs by date range (Admin only)
GET https://localhost:7004/logs/date-range?from=2024-11-13T00:00:00&to=2024-11-13T23:59:59
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Accept: application/json

### Note: 
# Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE with actual JWT token from UsersService login
# Replace YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE with admin JWT token (username: admin, password: password123)
